quote: So it begins. The trivia of medicine is my domain now. Every runny nose, stubbed toe, pimple on a cheek becomes my responsibility.
Missing? The captain is missing? It seems I've found myself on a Voyage of the Damned. Very well, please advise the highest ranking officer who is not missing to see me at his earliest convenience.
I'm a doctor, Mister Neelix, not a decorator.

A nebula? What were we doing in a nebula? No wait, don't tell me. We were 'investigating'. That's all we do around here. Why pretend we're going home at all, all we're going to do is 'investigate' every cubic millimetre of this quadrant, aren't we?
There's one more request... something of a personal nature... I would like... a name.
Mister Neelix, just because a man changes his drink order doesn't mean he's posessed by an alien.

EMH: 'You should consider it a high complement. Throughout history men have fought over the love of a woman. Why, I can quote you autopsy reports from duels as far back as 1538.' 

 Kes: 'That's not funny.' 

 EMH: 'It's not meant to be. You've always been interested in autopsies.'

Kes: 'On my homeworld, it's so much simpler. You choose a mate for life; there's no distrust, no jealousy, no envy, no betrayal…' 

 EMH: 'Hm. Your homeworld must have very dry literature.'
I'm not just working anymore, I'm living.
I am programmed to be heroic when the need arises.
Welcome to sickbay. Take a number.
Between impulse and action, there is a realm of good taste begging for your acquaintance!

One : 'Joke, a verbal comment or gesture designed to provoke laughter.'

 EMH : 'I see you've got your mothers sense of humour.'
I'm a Doctor, not a battery!
I'm a doctor, not a dragonslayer!
It's quite disconcerting to know that all someone has to do is flick a switch to turn me into Mr. Hyde

Tuvok, I understand, You are a Vulcan man, You have just gone without, For seven years, about. Paris, please find a way, To load a hypospray, I will give you the sign, Just aim for his behind. Hormones are raging, Synapses blazing, It's all so veeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeerrrry illogical!
The Vulcan brain; a puzzle wrapped inside an enigma housed inside a cranium.
Welcome to Sickbay. How may I help you today?
When did it become a crime to enjoy a sensation or two? Of course, you'd be the last person to understand that.

EMH : 'Is there anything in your spiritual programming about making peace with your enemies?' 

 Iden : 'It's difficult to make peace with people whose sole purpose is to kill you.'
I'd never admit this to anyone else, but there was a time when I would have given anything to be flesh and blood. But I've come to realize that being a hologram is far superior.
I am a doctor, not a peeping Tom, there's nothing I haven't seen before.

You know, if you skip lunch, the result might be a lower blood sugar level, which could… I'm sorry. It's in my program. I see something wrong, I must attempt to diagnose it.

EMH: 'I shouldn't have to remind you: I'm a doctor…' 

 Torres: '…not an engineer. Right, but…
I'm a doctor, not a performer.
I'm a doctor, not a counterinsurgent.

EMH: 'I'm a doctor, not a database.' 

 Henry Starling: 'I'd say you're a little bit of both.'
